Source.Name: glib2
Source.Summary: Low level C library containing data structure handling and interfaces
Source.Description: GLib is the low-level core library that forms the basis for projects such as GTK+ and GNOME. It provides data structure handling for C, portability wrappers, and interfaces for such runtime functionality as an event loop, threads, dynamic loading, and an object system.
